346
00:22:12,100 --> 00:22:13,800
They kill you for stuff like this.

347
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:15,200
This is very serious shit.

348
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:19,700
- There's no time like now. If we pull this off...
- There's no time like now? Are you crazy?

349
00:22:19,700 --> 00:22:21,200
We're not weapons dealers.

350
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:25,200
Would you kindly shut up?
Man, you're so negative. I'm trying to think.

351
00:22:25,300 --> 00:22:26,700
Hey.

352
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:29,000
We're smart, right?

353
00:22:30,100 --> 00:22:31,100
Yeah.

354
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,400
Now, we could do this.

355
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:34,400
- We could do this.
- Oh, man.

356
00:22:40,500 --> 00:22:42,300
What do we do with this shit?

357
00:22:43,300 --> 00:22:47,000
Well, first we need to store it.
And I know the perfect place.

358
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:55,000
Hey, this place gives me the creeps.

359
00:22:56,100 --> 00:22:58,000
Yeah, it's supposed to.

360
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:20,100
- Hey, friend, what's up?
- Hey, Elwood.

361
00:23:20,100 --> 00:23:21,800
What's going on, man?

362
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:25,200
Nothing much. I got some stuff I need to store.
Can you help me out?

363
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:26,900
Sure thing, man.

364
00:23:26,900 --> 00:23:30,100
Hey, are we gonna party afterwards?

365
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:31,900
Does the Pope shit in the woods?

366
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:37,400
Hey, we can do a lot of things
with the cash we make off this.

367
00:23:38,900 --> 00:23:40,600
You know what I'm saying?

368
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:46,100
Cos I was thinking about opening up a bar,
a nice, classy place.

369
00:23:46,100 --> 00:23:48,800
Me and you'd be partners.

370
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,000
What do you think?

371
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:52,000
Sure.

372
00:23:52,100 --> 00:23:53,300
Why not?

373
00:23:58,700 --> 00:23:59,700
Fuck!

374
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:07,600
This one ready to go?

375
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:09,400
Yeah, almost. Almost.

376
00:24:10,500 --> 00:24:11,500
Easy.

377
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,800
You be all right?

378
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:31,200
Yeah.

379
00:24:31,300 --> 00:24:34,600
- You ain't out in 30, I'm coming in.
- Don't worry, I'll be fine.

380
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:53,600
Turkish music

381
00:24:56,900 --> 00:24:59,800
- Elwood, how are you, my friend?
- Hey, Davood, how are you?

382
00:24:59,800 --> 00:25:04,200
- Are you hungry? You want something to eat?
- Oh, no, I'm fine, thanks. I'd better get up.

383
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:06,700
Say hi to your sister, all right?

384
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:15,100
A lot of guns.

385
00:25:15,100 --> 00:25:16,800
Where did you get all this stuff?

386
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:18,900
Santa Claus.

387
00:25:18,900 --> 00:25:22,200
Santa Claus. That's funny.

388
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:25,400
He came down the chimney
and put it under the tree, hm?

389
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:26,400
Yup.

390
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:33,600
So...

391
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:36,200
...how about this?

392
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:41,500
I give you 20 kilos on top of my next shipment,

393
00:25:41,600 --> 00:25:44,600
and you cook that
along with my share of the shipment,

394
00:25:45,400 --> 00:25:47,000
and you make a lot of money.

395
00:25:48,700 --> 00:25:50,400
- 20 kilos?
- Mm.

396
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:53,600
No. I want cash.

397
00:25:55,100 --> 00:25:56,300
25.

398
00:25:57,600 --> 00:26:00,900
Look, I know somebody else
who's very interested in this merchandise.

399
00:26:02,300 --> 00:26:04,000
OK.

400
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:06,000
Maybe they'll pay you cash.

401
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:08,700
35.

402
00:26:08,800 --> 00:26:10,100
29.

403
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:14,400
I hate to break that 30 mark.
It's a religious thing with me.

404
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:17,500
I'm afraid you'll have to,
cos 30 kilos is my final offer.

405
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:37,900
He's sending us 30Ks. One week.

406
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:40,400
30Ks?

407
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:42,600
Holy shit! That's, er...

408
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:44,900
- A lot.
- Well, how do we cook that much?

409
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:48,400
- It'll take us, like, a year.
- It's gonna be cool.

