412
00:27:10,300 --> 00:27:13,700
Politically, Mr Gorbachev
has never been more vulnerable.

413
00:27:15,700 --> 00:27:17,500
This is really impressive.

414
00:27:18,900 --> 00:27:20,500
Hey, guys, careful with my shit.

415
00:27:22,900 --> 00:27:25,100
You're pretty well equipped for a Spec Four.

416
00:27:25,100 --> 00:27:26,600
I got receipts for everything.

417
00:27:26,700 --> 00:27:27,900
I'm sure you do.

418
00:27:27,900 --> 00:27:29,500
Hey, Top, look at this.

419
00:27:30,600 --> 00:27:33,300
Check and see if there's anything inside.

420
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:41,800
Nothing.

421
00:27:45,700 --> 00:27:47,500
Hm? Mm-hm.

422
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:50,600
I'll bet this don't come cheap.

423
00:27:52,100 --> 00:27:55,300
This ain't exactly regulation stuff here,
is it, soldier?

424
00:27:55,300 --> 00:27:57,300
I don't really know.

425
00:27:58,500 --> 00:27:59,700
No, I guess not.

426
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:05,300
Look, I'm gonna come round here tomorrow.
I want this place looking like a regular quarters.

427
00:28:05,300 --> 00:28:06,700
You follow?

428
00:28:06,700 --> 00:28:10,700
Look, I know it ain't exactly regulation,
but the last Top didn't seem to mind.

429
00:28:11,700 --> 00:28:14,100
Well, him and me are a bit different.

430
00:28:17,600 --> 00:28:19,200
Look, Top,

431
00:28:19,300 --> 00:28:21,500
is there a way you and I could talk in private?

432
00:28:21,500 --> 00:28:23,400
These guys kinda make me nervous.

433
00:28:42,200 --> 00:28:44,000
Does it really have to play this way, Top?

434
00:28:44,100 --> 00:28:46,200
How do you suggest we play it?

435
00:28:48,100 --> 00:28:50,200
Well, what is it you want?

436
00:28:51,300 --> 00:28:55,200
I mean, you and me, I think we...
I think we got a lot in common.

437
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:57,500
Barriers are coming down in Hungary.

438
00:28:57,600 --> 00:29:00,300
So must they fall
throughout all of Eastern Europe.

439
00:29:00,300 --> 00:29:04,200
For example, I see you're an admirer
of Japanese technology.

440
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:05,700
No problem.

441
00:29:05,800 --> 00:29:07,100
The TV's yours.

442
00:29:07,200 --> 00:29:09,500
What I'm trying to say is,

443
00:29:10,700 --> 00:29:13,000
what's it gonna take
for you and me to make nice?

444
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:15,400
Are you saying what I think you're saying?

445
00:29:19,300 --> 00:29:21,300
The world has waited...

446
00:29:29,300 --> 00:29:31,000
There's your answer.

447
00:30:09,500 --> 00:30:11,100
Elwood.

448
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:13,200
Hey, this'll take a second.

449
00:30:13,300 --> 00:30:15,700
- I'll meet you down there.
- All right.

450
00:30:19,700 --> 00:30:21,500
Where are you off to in such a hurry?

451
00:30:21,600 --> 00:30:24,100
Nowhere, really.
Just had a couple of things to do.

452
00:30:24,100 --> 00:30:27,300
You're always off with your buddies.
I never see you any more.

453
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:29,500
It's just cos I've been really busy.

454
00:30:29,600 --> 00:30:31,600
- Busy?
- Yeah.

455
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:38,000
- It's the guest list.
- Guest list?

456
00:30:38,100 --> 00:30:40,500
Party. Are you still helping me?

457
00:30:40,500 --> 00:30:42,800
Oh, the par... Yeah. Sure. Definitely.

458
00:30:42,900 --> 00:30:45,200
We found out the Colonel's related
to the Iron Boar.

459
00:30:45,300 --> 00:30:48,300
- The Iron what?
- The Iron Boar, as in male pig.

460
00:30:48,300 --> 00:30:51,700
I had a lawyer trace his family tree,
and he's a distant relative

461
00:30:51,700 --> 00:30:53,900
of a Civil War hero, John Bell Hood.

462
00:30:53,900 --> 00:30:56,100
They called him the Iron Boar.

463
00:30:56,100 --> 00:30:59,600
He'll announce it to General Lancaster
at the party, to help his promotion.

464
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:08,200
Sergeant Lee's daughter.

465
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:10,500
That's Top's daughter? You're kidding.

466
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:14,100
See something you like, Elwood?

467
00:31:22,700 --> 00:31:24,700
Nice dive.

468
00:31:27,100 --> 00:31:28,400
Thanks.

469
00:31:28,500 --> 00:31:30,700
The new Top, what do you think he's up to?

470
00:31:30,700 --> 00:31:33,500
